<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Konrad von Gemmingen</head><p>Der Rat teilt mit, dass er die betroffenen Nürnberger zur Ausrichtung Hermann Scheffers, Armmann des Adressaten, wegen der schuldigen Salzscheiben des H. Tartschenfeind angewiesen hat, und verweist auf den Rechtsweg.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_578" id="288r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_578_r2l20"><expan>Conr<ex>ad</ex></expan> von Gemmingen </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_578_r2l21"><expan>L<ex>ieber</ex></expan> <expan>Conr<ex>ad</ex></expan> als Jr vns <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt von <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>s</expan> arm <expan>man<ex>n</ex>s</expan> <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>H<ex>er</ex>man</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l22"><expan>ſcheͣff<ex>er</ex>s</expan> / dem der <expan cert="unknown">h</expan>  tartſchenveynd etlıch ſcheıben ſalcʒ ſchuldıg ſey </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l23">dıe er Jm <expan>v<ex>er</ex>bürgt</expan> hab etc / Das haben wır wol <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> / Vnd haben </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l24">vmb <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> wıllen . dıe <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> dıe das angeet / dıe yecʒ anheim geweſen </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l25">ſeyn . beſandt vnd <expan>fleıſſıkl<ex>ich</ex></expan> mit Jn geredt / dem <expan>vorgen<ex>anten</ex></expan> <expan>H<ex>er</ex>man</expan> ſcheͣffer </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l26"><expan>awſʒrıchtu<ex>n</ex>g</expan> ʒutun . vnd ſehen auch gern daʒ es beſchehe . Beſcheͣhe es </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l27">aber . niht ſo mag der <expan>vorg<ex>ena</ex>nt<ex>e</ex></expan> eẅr armman wol ʒu vns <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan> oder </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l28"><expan>ſein<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>ſcheinbott<ex>en</ex></expan> mıt <expan>ſeine<ex>m</ex></expan> <expan>volle<ex>n</ex></expan> gwalt . ʒu vns <expan>ſchık<ex>en</ex></expan> ſo wellen wır </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l29">Jn <expan>freẅntl<ex>ich</ex></expan> ſleẅnıgs <expan>rechte<ex>n</ex></expan> von den <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>helff<ex>en</ex></expan> vor des </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l30">Reıchs <expan>Rıcht<ex>er</ex></expan> bey vns ʒu <expan>Nür<ex>emberg</ex></expan> wenn wır des ermant <expan>w<ex>er</ex>den</expan> . ſo </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l31"><expan>dıeſ<ex>elben</ex></expan> dıe <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> bey vns anheim ſein vnd man gerıcht bey vns </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_line_1592207001467_4182">haben ſol . Denn wo wır <expan>eẅr<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>erberk<ex>eit</ex></expan> lıeb <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> dıenſt etc </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_578_r2l34"><expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> <expan>f<ex>er</ex>ıa</expan> v<hi rend="sup">a</hi> <expan>p<ex>oſt</ex></expan> <expan>Conu<ex>er</ex>ſıon<ex>is</ex></expan> Paulȷ </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_578" id="288r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab><expan>Conr<ex>ad</ex></expan> von Gemmingen </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieber</ex></expan>
<expan>Conr<ex>ad</ex></expan>, als ir uns
                            <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt von
                            <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>s</expan> arm<expan>man<ex>n</ex>s</expan>
<expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>, <expan>H<ex>er</ex>man</expan>
<expan>Scheͣff<ex>er</ex>s</expan>, dem der <expan cert="unknown">H.</expan>
                        Tartschenveynd etlich scheiben salcz schuldig sey, die er im
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>bürgt</expan> hab etc., das haben wir wol
                                <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> und haben umb
                            <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan> willen die <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>,
                        die das angeet, die yecz anheim gewesen seyn, besandt und
                                <expan>fleissikl<ex>ich</ex></expan> mit in geredt, dem
                                <expan>vorgen<ex>anten</ex></expan>
<expan>H<ex>er</ex>man</expan> Scheͣffer
                            <expan>awszrichtu<ex>n</ex>g</expan> zutun, und sehen auch gern, daz es
                        beschehe. Bescheͣhe es aber niht, so mag der
                                <expan>vorg<ex>ena</ex>nt<ex>e</ex></expan> ewr armman wol zu uns
                                <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan> oder <expan>sein<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>scheinbott<ex>en</ex></expan> mit <expan>seine<ex>m</ex></expan>
<expan>volle<ex>n</ex></expan> gwalt zu uns <expan>schik<ex>en</ex></expan>,
                        so wellen wir in <expan>frewntl<ex>ich</ex></expan> slewnigs
                                <expan>rechte<ex>n</ex></expan> von den
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>helff<ex>en</ex></expan> vor des reichs
                            <expan>richt<ex>er</ex></expan> bey uns zu
                            <expan>Nür<ex>emberg</ex></expan>, wenn wir des ermant
                                <expan>w<ex>er</ex>den</expan>, so <expan>dies<ex>elben</ex></expan>
                        die <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> bey uns anheim sein und man gericht bey
                        uns haben sol. Denn wo wir <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>erberk<ex>eit</ex></expan> lieb <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> dienst
                        etc. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> v<hi rend="sup">a</hi>
<expan>p<ex>ost</ex></expan>
<expan>conv<ex>er</ex>sion<ex>is</ex></expan> Pauli. </ab>
</div>
</div></body>
